{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":946,"text":"What is so special about the human brain?"},{"time":3340,"text":"Why is it that we study other animals"},{"time":5552,"text":"instead of them studying us?"},{"time":7673,"text":"What does a human brain have or do"},{"time":9471,"text":"that no other brain does?"},{"time":11204,"text":"When I became interested\nin these questions about 10 years ago,"},{"time":14052,"text":"scientists thought they knew\nwhat different brains were made of."},{"time":16994,"text":"Though it was based on very little evidence,"},{"time":18723,"text":"many scientists thought that all mammalian brains,"},{"time":20910,"text":"including the human brain,"},{"time":22635,"text":"were made in the same way,"},{"time":23935,"text":"with a number of neurons that was always"},{"time":25437,"text":"proportional to the size of the brain."},{"time":27668,"text":"This means that two brains of the same size,"},{"time":29744,"text":"like these two, with a respectable 400 grams,"},{"time":33292,"text":"should have similar numbers of neurons."},{"time":35844,"text":"Now, if neurons are the functional"},{"time":37640,"text":"information processing units of the brain,"},{"time":40543,"text":"then the owners of these two brains"},{"time":42135,"text":"should have similar cognitive abilities."},{"time":44864,"text":"And yet, one is a chimp,"},{"time":47213,"text":"and the other is a cow."},{"time":49850,"text":"Now maybe cows have a really rich"},{"time":52212,"text":"internal mental life and are so smart"},{"time":54465,"text":"that they choose not to let us realize it,"},{"time":58268,"text":"but we eat them."},{"time":59713,"text":"I think most people will agree"},{"time":61412,"text":"that chimps are capable of much more complex,"},{"time":63413,"text":"elaborate and flexible behaviors than cows are."},{"time":66469,"text":"So this is a first indication that the"},{"time":68401,"text":"\"all brains are made the same way\" scenario"},{"time":70434,"text":"is not quite right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72105,"text":"But let's play along."},{"time":73451,"text":"If all brains were made the same way"},{"time":75229,"text":"and you were to compare animals\nwith brains of different sizes,"},{"time":78141,"text":"larger brains should always have more neurons"},{"time":80323,"text":"than smaller brains,\nand the larger the brain,"},{"time":82646,"text":"the more cognitively able its owner should be."},{"time":85668,"text":"So the largest brain around should also be"},{"time":87804,"text":"the most cognitively able."},{"time":90093,"text":"And here comes the bad news:"},{"time":91674,"text":"Our brain, not the largest one around."},{"time":94431,"text":"It seems quite vexing."},{"time":95986,"text":"Our brain weighs between 1.2 and 1.5 kilos,"},{"time":98721,"text":"but elephant brains weigh between four and five kilos,"},{"time":102038,"text":"and whale brains can weigh up to nine kilos,"},{"time":104623,"text":"which is why scientists used to resort to saying"},{"time":109361,"text":"that our brain must be special"},{"time":111518,"text":"to explain our cognitive abilities."},{"time":114380,"text":"It must be really extraordinary,"},{"time":117326,"text":"an exception to the rule."},{"time":119303,"text":"Theirs may be bigger, but ours is better,"},{"time":122529,"text":"and it could be better, for example,"},{"time":124404,"text":"in that it seems larger than it should be,"},{"time":126515,"text":"with a much larger cerebral cortex\nthan we should have"},{"time":129213,"text":"for the size of our bodies."},{"time":130752,"text":"So that would give us extra cortex"},{"time":132404,"text":"to do more interesting things\nthan just operating the body."},{"time":135364,"text":"That's because the size of the brain"},{"time":137043,"text":"usually follows the size of the body."},{"time":139376,"text":"So the main reason for saying that"},{"time":141693,"text":"our brain is larger than it should be"},{"time":143780,"text":"actually comes from comparing ourselves"},{"time":145552,"text":"to great apes."},{"time":147238,"text":"Gorillas can be two to three times larger than we are,"},{"time":149832,"text":"so their brains should also be larger than ours,"},{"time":152253,"text":"but instead it's the other way around."},{"time":154198,"text":"Our brain is three times larger than a gorilla brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157133,"text":"The human brain also seems special"},{"time":159253,"text":"in the amount of energy that it uses."},{"time":161500,"text":"Although it weighs only two percent of the body,"},{"time":164249,"text":"it alone uses 25 percent of all the energy"},{"time":167692,"text":"that your body requires to run per day."},{"time":170155,"text":"That's 500 calories out of a total of 2,000 calories,"},{"time":173508,"text":"just to keep your brain working."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175913,"text":"So the human brain is larger than it should be,"},{"time":178841,"text":"it uses much more energy than it should,"},{"time":180867,"text":"so it's special."},{"time":182325,"text":"And this is where the story started to bother me."},{"time":184896,"text":"In biology, we look for rules"},{"time":186567,"text":"that apply to all animals and to life in general,"},{"time":189413,"text":"so why should the rules of evolution"},{"time":191263,"text":"apply to everybody else but not to us?"},{"time":194905,"text":"Maybe the problem was with the basic assumption"},{"time":197102,"text":"that all brains are made in the same way."},{"time":198973,"text":"Maybe two brains of a similar size"},{"time":200572,"text":"can actually be made of\nvery different numbers of neurons."},{"time":203163,"text":"Maybe a very large brain"},{"time":204770,"text":"does not necessarily have more neurons"},{"time":206610,"text":"than a more modest-sized brain."},{"time":208831,"text":"Maybe the human brain \nactually has the most neurons"},{"time":211840,"text":"of any brain, regardless of its size,"},{"time":214413,"text":"especially in the cerebral cortex."},{"time":216507,"text":"So this to me became"},{"time":218059,"text":"the important question to answer:"},{"time":219788,"text":"how many neurons does the human brain have,"},{"time":222188,"text":"and how does that compare to other animals?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":224710,"text":"Now, you may have heard or read somewhere"},{"time":227133,"text":"that we have 100 billion neurons,"},{"time":229244,"text":"so 10 years ago, I asked my colleagues"},{"time":231330,"text":"if they knew where this number came from."},{"time":233169,"text":"But nobody did."},{"time":234627,"text":"I've been digging through the literature"},{"time":236080,"text":"for the original reference for that number,"},{"time":238138,"text":"and I could never find it."},{"time":239921,"text":"It seems that nobody had actually ever counted"},{"time":242660,"text":"the number of neurons in the human brain,"},{"time":244194,"text":"or in any other brain for that matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246693,"text":"So I came up with my own way\nto count cells in the brain,"},{"time":250228,"text":"and it essentially consists of"},{"time":252336,"text":"dissolving that brain into soup."},{"time":255581,"text":"It works like this:"},{"time":257618,"text":"You take a brain, or parts of that brain,"},{"time":260745,"text":"and you dissolve it in detergent,"},{"time":262489,"text":"which destroys the cell membranes"},{"time":263998,"text":"but keeps the cell nuclei intact,"},{"time":266434,"text":"so you end up with a suspension of free nuclei"},{"time":269574,"text":"that looks like this,"},{"time":271355,"text":"like a clear soup."},{"time":272628,"text":"This soup contains all the nuclei"},{"time":274519,"text":"that once were a mouse brain."},{"time":276573,"text":"Now, the beauty of a soup is that because it is soup,"},{"time":279603,"text":"you can agitate it and make those nuclei"},{"time":282501,"text":"be distributed homogeneously in the liquid,"},{"time":284472,"text":"so that now by looking under the microscope"},{"time":286453,"text":"at just four or five samples\nof this homogeneous solution,"},{"time":290536,"text":"you can count nuclei, and therefore tell"},{"time":293072,"text":"how many cells that brain had."},{"time":294751,"text":"It's simple, it's straightforward,"},{"time":296376,"text":"and it's really fast."},{"time":297810,"text":"So we've used that method to count neurons"},{"time":299807,"text":"in dozens of different species so far,"},{"time":302118,"text":"and it turns out that all brains"},{"time":303807,"text":"are not made the same way."},{"time":306389,"text":"Take rodents and primates, for instance:"},{"time":308576,"text":"In larger rodent brains, the average size"},{"time":310860,"text":"of the neuron increases,"},{"time":312546,"text":"so the brain inflates very rapidly"},{"time":315145,"text":"and gains size much faster than it gains neurons."},{"time":318310,"text":"But primate brains gain neurons"},{"time":320013,"text":"without the average neuron becoming any larger,"},{"time":322472,"text":"which is a very economical way"},{"time":323997,"text":"to add neurons to your brain."},{"time":325650,"text":"The result is that a primate brain"},{"time":327414,"text":"will always have more neurons than\na rodent brain of the same size,"},{"time":330581,"text":"and the larger the brain,"},{"time":332064,"text":"the larger this difference will be."},{"time":334278,"text":"Well, what about our brain then?"},{"time":336381,"text":"We found that we have, on average,"},{"time":338065,"text":"86 billion neurons,"},{"time":339850,"text":"16 billion of which are in the cerebral cortex,"},{"time":342849,"text":"and if you consider that the cerebral cortex"},{"time":344930,"text":"is the seat of functions like"},{"time":348024,"text":"awareness and logical and abstract reasoning,"},{"time":351161,"text":"and that 16 billion is the most neurons"},{"time":354145,"text":"that any cortex has,"},{"time":356766,"text":"I think this is the simplest explanation"},{"time":358484,"text":"for our remarkable cognitive abilities."},{"time":361626,"text":"But just as important is what\nthe 86 billion neurons mean."},{"time":364847,"text":"Because we found that the relationship"},{"time":366376,"text":"between the size of the brain\nand its number of neurons"},{"time":368728,"text":"could be described mathematically,"},{"time":370355,"text":"we could calculate what a human brain"},{"time":372573,"text":"would look like if it was made like a rodent brain."},{"time":375247,"text":"So, a rodent brain with 86 billion neurons"},{"time":378821,"text":"would weigh 36 kilos."},{"time":381942,"text":"That's not possible."},{"time":383575,"text":"A brain that huge would be crushed"},{"time":385481,"text":"by its own weight,"},{"time":386665,"text":"and this impossible brain would go"},{"time":388252,"text":"in the body of 89 tons."},{"time":392023,"text":"I don't think it looks like us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394157,"text":"So this brings us to a very important\nconclusion already,"},{"time":396710,"text":"which is that we are not rodents."},{"time":399357,"text":"The human brain is not a large rat brain."},{"time":402625,"text":"Compared to a rat, we might seem special, yes,"},{"time":405253,"text":"but that's not a fair comparison to make,"},{"time":407473,"text":"given that we know that we are not rodents."},{"time":409562,"text":"We are primates,"},{"time":410952,"text":"so the correct comparison is to other primates."},{"time":413726,"text":"And there, if you do the math,"},{"time":414953,"text":"you find that a generic primate"},{"time":417739,"text":"with 86 billion neurons"},{"time":419669,"text":"would have a brain of about 1.2 kilos,"},{"time":422672,"text":"which seems just right,"},{"time":424561,"text":"in a body of some 66 kilos,"},{"time":426533,"text":"which in my case is exactly right,"},{"time":429178,"text":"which brings us to a very unsurprising"},{"time":431798,"text":"but still incredibly important conclusion:"},{"time":434767,"text":"I am a primate."},{"time":436108,"text":"And all of you are primates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438806,"text":"And so was Darwin."},{"time":440706,"text":"I love to think that Darwin\nwould have really appreciated this."},{"time":443646,"text":"His brain, like ours,"},{"time":445613,"text":"was made in the image of other primate brains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449124,"text":"So the human brain may be remarkable, yes,"},{"time":451426,"text":"but it is not special in its number of neurons."},{"time":454207,"text":"It is just a large primate brain."},{"time":456062,"text":"I think that's a very humbling and sobering thought"},{"time":459106,"text":"that should remind us of our place in nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462169,"text":"Why does it cost so much energy, then?"},{"time":464813,"text":"Well, other people have figured out"},{"time":466260,"text":"how much energy the human brain"},{"time":467763,"text":"and that of other species costs,"},{"time":469170,"text":"and now that we knew how many neurons"},{"time":470822,"text":"each brain was made of, we could do the math."},{"time":473164,"text":"And it turns out that both human"},{"time":475030,"text":"and other brains cost about the same,"},{"time":477853,"text":"an average of six calories \nper billion neurons per day."},{"time":481274,"text":"So the total energetic cost of a brain"},{"time":483413,"text":"is a simple, linear function"},{"time":485447,"text":"of its number of neurons,"},{"time":487156,"text":"and it turns out that the human brain"},{"time":489339,"text":"costs just as much energy as you would expect."},{"time":493180,"text":"So the reason why the human brain"},{"time":495271,"text":"costs so much energy is simply because"},{"time":496943,"text":"it has a huge number of neurons,"},{"time":498926,"text":"and because we are primates"},{"time":500411,"text":"with many more neurons for a given body size"},{"time":502910,"text":"than any other animal,"},{"time":504432,"text":"the relative cost of our brain is large,"},{"time":507972,"text":"but just because we're primates,\nnot because we're special."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510973,"text":"Last question, then:"},{"time":512163,"text":"how did we come by this\nremarkable number of neurons,"},{"time":515278,"text":"and in particular, if great apes"},{"time":517178,"text":"are larger than we are,"},{"time":518733,"text":"why don't they have a larger brain \nthan we do, with more neurons?"},{"time":522498,"text":"When we realized how much expensive it is"},{"time":524588,"text":"to have a lot of neurons in the brain, I figured,"},{"time":526921,"text":"maybe there's a simple reason."},{"time":528924,"text":"They just can't afford the energy"},{"time":530607,"text":"for both a large body \nand a large number of neurons."},{"time":533557,"text":"So we did the math."},{"time":534986,"text":"We calculated on the one hand"},{"time":536586,"text":"how much energy a primate gets per day"},{"time":538527,"text":"from eating raw foods,"},{"time":539877,"text":"and on the other hand, how much energy"},{"time":541914,"text":"a body of a certain size costs"},{"time":543678,"text":"and how much energy a brain of a\ncertain number of neurons costs,"},{"time":547065,"text":"and we looked for the combinations"},{"time":548554,"text":"of body size and number of brain neurons"},{"time":550965,"text":"that a primate could afford"},{"time":552235,"text":"if it ate a certain number of hours per day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554783,"text":"And what we found is that"},{"time":556599,"text":"because neurons are so expensive,"},{"time":558311,"text":"there is a tradeoff between\nbody size and number of neurons."},{"time":561681,"text":"So a primate that eats eight hours per day"},{"time":564632,"text":"can afford at most 53 billion neurons,"},{"time":567656,"text":"but then its body cannot be any bigger"},{"time":569383,"text":"than 25 kilos."},{"time":571337,"text":"To weigh any more than that,"},{"time":573038,"text":"it has to give up neurons."},{"time":574807,"text":"So it's either a large body"},{"time":577460,"text":"or a large number of neurons."},{"time":578955,"text":"When you eat like a primate,"},{"time":580320,"text":"you can't afford both."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582556,"text":"One way out of this metabolic limitation"},{"time":584520,"text":"would be to spend even more hours per day eating,"},{"time":587921,"text":"but that gets dangerous,"},{"time":589284,"text":"and past a certain point, it's just not possible."},{"time":592003,"text":"Gorillas and orangutans, for instance,"},{"time":593540,"text":"afford about 30 billion neurons"},{"time":595463,"text":"by spending eight and a half hours per day eating,"},{"time":598429,"text":"and that seems to be about as much as they can do."},{"time":601545,"text":"Nine hours of feeding per day"},{"time":603336,"text":"seems to be the practical limit for a primate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606607,"text":"What about us?"},{"time":608398,"text":"With our 86 billion neurons"},{"time":609998,"text":"and 60 to 70 kilos of body mass,"},{"time":613033,"text":"we should have to spend over nine hours"},{"time":616594,"text":"per day every single day feeding,"},{"time":620169,"text":"which is just not feasible."},{"time":622208,"text":"If we ate like a primate,"},{"time":624042,"text":"we should not be here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626295,"text":"How did we get here, then?"},{"time":628422,"text":"Well, if our brain costs just as much energy"},{"time":631157,"text":"as it should, and if we can't spend"},{"time":632880,"text":"every waking hour of the day feeding,"},{"time":636554,"text":"then the only alternative, really,"},{"time":638465,"text":"is to somehow get more energy"},{"time":640423,"text":"out of the same foods."},{"time":642376,"text":"And remarkably, that matches exactly"},{"time":646176,"text":"what our ancestors are believed to have invented"},{"time":649213,"text":"one and a half million years ago,"},{"time":651052,"text":"when they invented cooking."},{"time":653834,"text":"To cook is to use fire"},{"time":655804,"text":"to pre-digest foods outside of your body."},{"time":659604,"text":"Cooked foods are softer, so they're easier to chew"},{"time":662210,"text":"and to turn completely into mush in your mouth,"},{"time":664773,"text":"so that allows them to be completely digested"},{"time":666925,"text":"and absorbed in your gut,"},{"time":668361,"text":"which makes them yield much more\nenergy in much less time."},{"time":672016,"text":"So cooking frees time for us to do"},{"time":674505,"text":"much more interesting things with our day"},{"time":676567,"text":"and with our neurons"},{"time":678047,"text":"than just thinking about food,"},{"time":679952,"text":"looking for food, and gobbling down food"},{"time":681656,"text":"all day long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682881,"text":"So because of cooking, what once was"},{"time":685380,"text":"a major liability, this large,"},{"time":687733,"text":"dangerously expensive brain with a lot of neurons,"},{"time":690766,"text":"could now become a major asset,"},{"time":692802,"text":"now that we could both afford \nthe energy for a lot of neurons"},{"time":696056,"text":"and the time to do interesting things with them."},{"time":698559,"text":"So I think this explains why the human brain"},{"time":700533,"text":"grew to become so large so fast in evolution,"},{"time":703773,"text":"all of the while remaining just a primate brain."},{"time":707670,"text":"With this large brain now affordable by cooking,"},{"time":710444,"text":"we went rapidly from raw foods to culture,"},{"time":713357,"text":"agriculture, civilization, grocery stores,"},{"time":715963,"text":"electricity, refrigerators,"},{"time":717588,"text":"all of those things that nowadays"},{"time":719195,"text":"allow us to get all the energy we need"},{"time":721237,"text":"for the whole day in a single sitting"},{"time":724019,"text":"at your favorite fast food joint."},{"time":726973,"text":"So what once was a solution"},{"time":729410,"text":"now became the problem,"},{"time":731109,"text":"and ironically, we look for the solution in raw food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736626,"text":"So what is the human advantage?"},{"time":739182,"text":"What is it that we have"},{"time":740685,"text":"that no other animal has?"},{"time":743220,"text":"My answer is that we have the largest number"},{"time":745568,"text":"of neurons in the cerebral cortex,"},{"time":747040,"text":"and I think that's the simplest explanation"},{"time":748884,"text":"for our remarkable cognitive abilities."},{"time":750897,"text":"And what is it that we do that no other animal does,"},{"time":754124,"text":"and which I believe was fundamental"},{"time":756093,"text":"to allow us to reach that large,"},{"time":759176,"text":"largest number of neurons in the cortex?"},{"time":761398,"text":"In two words, we cook."},{"time":763613,"text":"No other animal cooks its food. Only humans do."},{"time":767179,"text":"And I think that's how we got to become human."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770049,"text":"Studying the human brain changed \nthe way I think about food."},{"time":772509,"text":"I now look at my kitchen,"},{"time":774154,"text":"and I bow to it,"},{"time":775624,"text":"and I thank my ancestors for coming up"},{"time":777329,"text":"with the invention that probably made us humans."},{"time":779229,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":781361,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}